About this item

  • 100% WHEY VANILLA PROTEIN POWDER: Each serving contains 25g protein, 2g carbs, 130 calories, and only 1g sugar.
  • 5.5g BCAAs: As part of a complete amino acid profile that helps to repair and rebuild muscle, support strong bones, and build antibodies. Enjoy in a meal or as a snack to satisfy hunger!
  • EASY TO DIGEST: Made with high quality, cross-flow microfiltered 100% whey protein and pineapple bromelain, a natural digestive enzyme, for maximum absorption and fast digestion.
  • INFORMED CHOICE CERTIFIED: Quality you can trust, whatever your performance level. Keto, vegetarian and kosher friendly. Free of artificial colours, artificial flavours, preservatives, gluten, and more.
  • 62 SERVINGS PER CONTAINER - 1 SCOOP PER SERVING: Add one 32g scoop into 250mL (8oz) of your favourite beverage. Shake it and enjoy anytime of the day!

Eva Blaskovic
4.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality Protein with Stevia, Only 2g Sugar
Reviewed in Canada on September 13, 2023
Verified Purchase
Sept. 2023. This is a good product with stevia instead of sucralose or other artificial sweeteners, as well as both whey protein isolate and concentrate. It could stand to be a bit less sweet. There are no unnecessary additives and "junk" ingredients. I find this protein very effective when I train with heavy weights. The price has gone up a lot. It now comes in a bag instead of the plastic container, which is okay except that the ziplock is defective and the two sides will not fit together to close. I'm using three metal clips to keep the bag closed, but it is not airtight. I do recommend this protein for people who can consume whey (and I hope the ziplock closure defect gets fixed).

Update Oct. 2023: After I received my LeanFit, which at the time of purchase had shown the photo of the tub, I noticed more differences compared to the bag version (see photo). Fewer BCAAs and protein, more sugar. Also, soy is listed on the bag ingredients (possibly for allergen purposes), which the tub does not have. Several years ago, there was an organic version of the tub. That disappeared, but now the next change is that the bags have slightly different ingredients, with more sugar and less protein. It's still a good product, but this trend is disappointing. Also, many Amazon product photos are updated to include a disclaimer that the actual product received may not be exactly like the photo. If the actual product shipped does not include the same ingredients or amounts, how do we know what we're buying if it is not accurately shown in the photo or stated in the text? Fortunately, the photo of the bag now does appear for a different listing, so it's accurate.
